T1  - A Method for Determining the Appropriateness of National Planning in a Market Economy*
PY  - 1980
Y1  - 1980/09/01
DO  - 10.2307/1885499
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 95
IS  - 2
SP  - 261
EP  - 276
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - Meade demonstrates how, in the absence of futures markets for many commodities, indicative planning can supply economic agents with the requisite information about future market conditions. An incentive scheme designed to encourage agents to relay accurate information to central planners is introduced into Meade's model. It is then shown how the Groves and Loeb voting procedure can be used to determine whether an indicative planning program would be beneficial.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
